The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   BRIEFS
                  
	Tamluk, Aug. 13: The Opposition and the ruling Left Front agreed not to hold public gatherings for a fortnight at an all-party meeting that the Trinamul Congress attended for the first time in Nandigram today.     
	The parties also said they would not dig up roads in the area.        
	Durgapur: Four armed robbers freed their chief, Munna Khan, from the Asansol sub-divisional hospitals police cell on Wednesday evening. They pointed their guns at the two cops guarding Khan. Before they could react, the gang had freed Khan and left.                                                                                                                                                                   
